title: JUIâ€™s Candidate Muhammad Riaz wins PK-95 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ullema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) Candidate Muhammad Riaz has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-95, Kurram-I by securing 29,379 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Imran Khan who bagged 23,059 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 29.38 per cent.
